wikipedia_page.main: George Meads (7 July 1797 at Lindfield, Sussex – 30 July 1881 at Brighton, Sussex) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1825 to 1836.  He was mainly associated with Sussex and made 14 known appearances in first-class matches.
